<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="449" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,438,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Description.</emphasis>
Body mostly pale yellow. Vertex yellow with 
<number box="[814,828,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="2.0">2</number>
black spots. Face with black spot above each antennal pit (
<figureCitation box="[197,266,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1866,1889]" captionTargetBox="[169,1431,965,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[152,1435,965,1843]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Arboridia koreana sp. nov.: 1. Habitus. 3. Head. 5. Face. 7. Forewing. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov.: 2. Habitus. 4. Head. 6. Face. 8. Forewing. Scales: 0.5 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237530/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[250,266,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with one black spot at center of anterior margin. Mesonotum with two black triangles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1866,1889]" captionTargetBox="[169,1431,965,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[152,1435,965,1843]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Arboridia koreana sp. nov.: 1. Habitus. 3. Head. 5. Face. 7. Forewing. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov.: 2. Habitus. 4. Head. 6. Face. 8. Forewing. Scales: 0.5 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237530/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,168,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewings with brown zigzag pattern (
<figureCitation box="[622,690,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1866,1889]" captionTargetBox="[169,1431,965,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[152,1435,965,1843]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Arboridia koreana sp. nov.: 1. Habitus. 3. Head. 5. Face. 7. Forewing. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov.: 2. Habitus. 4. Head. 6. Face. 8. Forewing. Scales: 0.5 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237530/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[674,690,511,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow without pattern. Abdomen yellow without pattern.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,546,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Process of pygofer falcate with small dorsal tooth near base (
<figureCitation box="[1071,1156,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[1124,1156,547,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with 
<number box="[1422,1436,547,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="3.0">3</number>
macrosetae near middle and row of short setae from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[936,1023,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[992,1023,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style slender with 
<number box="[1266,1280,583,607]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="3.0">3</number>
apical points subequal in length to each other (
<figureCitation box="[523,607,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[576,607,619,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[920,1001,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[972,1001,618,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) with dorsal apodeme short, preatrium long and curved; dorsal apodeme with compressed anterior lobe and acute posterior projection; shaft compressed, tapered, as long as preatrium, curved dorsad with ventral margin angulate near base, apex narrowly rounded, without processes, very slender in caudal view (
<figureCitation box="[688,771,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[740,771,727,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective short and M- shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1254,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,825,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,820,1956]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Arboridia septempunctata sp. nov. 16. Aedeagus caudal view. 17. Aedeagus lateral view. 18. Style. 19. Connective. 20. Pygofer lobe lateral view. 21. Subgenital plate. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237532/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Fig. 
<number box="[1223,1254,727,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,438,787]" box="[199,916,762,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,762,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Measurements.</emphasis>
