(
<bibRefCitation author="Vilbaste" box="[867,1033,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="450" refString="Vilbaste, J. (1968) Uber die Zikadenfauna des Primorje Gebietes. Valgus, Tallinn, 195 pp." type="book" year="1968">
Vilbaste, 
<number box="[974,1033,295,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="450" value="1968.0">1968</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in forewing pattern and the black spot above the antennal pit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="450" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="4" pageNumber="450">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,367,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="450">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the characteristic 
<number box="[929,943,368,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="450" value="7.0">7</number>
prominent spots on the head, pronotum and mesonotum.
</paragraph>
